        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 8 at 6:08PM CDT by NWS Kansas City/Pleasant Hill MO</headline>
        <description>At 608 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Montrose, or 14 miles east of Butler, moving east at 40 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Clinton, Deepwater, Montrose, Coal, Brownington, La Due, and Truman
Lake.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 1000 PM CDT for
west central Missouri.</instruction>
